---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { evidenceMap, academicApplicationAngles } from "@data/research";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Evidence Map"
  description="How SCSDA public materials support Dr Daguang Han's UK and European academic applications without over-claiming."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell split">
      <div class="article">
        <p class="eyebrow">Academic-use evidence</p>
        <h2>What a UK or European academic reviewer should be able to infer.</h2>
        <p>
          This page connects the SCSDA institutional record with Dr Daguang
          Han's academic profile. It is intentionally written as an evidence
          map, not as a promotional biography. The goal is to show credible
          leadership in digital construction, smart infrastructure, BIM, digital
          twins, sensing and sustainable cities.
        </p>
        <p>
          Claims are framed with period labels and source boundaries. The site
          does not imply official government status, confidential access,
          public-security work or institutional scale beyond the available
          evidence.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="output-card">
        <h3>Best public positioning</h3>
        <p>
          SCSDA is an institutional research-platform website. It supports Dr
          Han's academic applications by evidencing founding leadership,
          platform construction, research-centre coordination and applied
          research translation.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is stronger and safer than making the domain a personal ability
          site: reviewers can read an institutional record first, then assess
          Dr Han's role inside it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section surface">
    <div class="shell section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Evidence chain</p>
        <h2>From source material to academic capability.</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        Each item below separates the underlying evidence from the safe public
        interpretation. This distinction is important for academic credibility.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="shell evidence-grid">
      {evidenceMap.map((item) => (
        <article class="evidence-card">
          <h3>{item.capability}</h3>
          <p>{item.whatItShows}</p>
          <dl>
            <div>
              <dt>Evidence basis</dt>
              <dd>{item.evidence}</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>Safe academic use</dt>
              <dd>{item.safeUse}</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Application value</p>
        <h2>How this site helps without looking like personal advertising.</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        The strongest route is to keep SCSDA as a research-organization site
        while making Dr Han's role legible through evidence-backed leadership
        language.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="shell claim-grid">
      {academicApplicationAngles.map((item) => (
        <article class="claim-card">
          <h3>{item.angle}</h3>
          <p>{item.text}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section tint">
    <div class="shell article narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">Boundary</p>
      <h2>What should not be inferred from this website.</h2>
      <p>
        The site should not be read as claiming that SCSDA is a government
        authority, that Dr Han alone completed every output, or that all legacy
        Chinese-site materials are suitable for international publication. It is
        a selective, public-facing and non-confidential evidence platform.
      </p>
      <div class="callout">
        Recommended CV/application wording: "Dr Daguang Han served as the
        principal responsible person and founding executive lead during SCSDA's
        early platform-construction period, coordinating research-centre
        development and applied research engagement in smart cities, digital
        built environments and sustainable infrastructure."
      </div>
      <p>
        Recommended website architecture: keep the English international site
        on the main SCSDA domain, keep historical Chinese material as a legacy
        or Chinese-language section, and keep Dr Han's full personal CV on his
        personal academic website. This separation improves credibility and
        reduces avoidable ambiguity.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
